<TITLE> 1 killed in crossfire in broad daylight in capital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 16 (bdnews24.com)  A murder suspect died from a head shot during a daytime shootout with RAB at the capital's Demra area on Tuesday. The suspect was wanted in 11 cases, including eight involving murder charges, said RAB. Assistant director of RAB-10 ABM Enamul Kabir told bdnews24.com that "Based on a tip-off, RAB conducted a drive to capture Md Assaduzzaman, a.k.a Rubel, at Sarulia Garden Road area of Demra at around 3pm." "Rubel started firing at the law enforcers to avoid arrest and died from a headshot wound as RAB fired back in self-defence", the RAB-10 chief said. RSB claimed that a foreign made revolver was recovered from the spot. b
